<span class="displayLabel">Description:&nbsp;</span>
<br />
Position Title and Location: <BR>Senior Associate Program – Austin, TX&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<BR>Position Overview<BR>GLG has traditionally been organized by industry specialty.&nbsp;&nbsp;Teams of client-facing Research Managers, each charged with specific industry specialization, function as thought partners to our clients.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to this industry-silo approach, GLG has a team of Research Managers who are capable of maneuvering in every industry.&nbsp;&nbsp;Members of the Client Solutions (CS) team serve as a single point of contact for clients who have a generalist approach to their research.<BR>Senior Associates work directly with their own book of clients and report indirectly to the Americas Head of their respective Research Team.&nbsp;&nbsp;Senior Associates design and facilitate the customized research solutions that our clients request, creating innovative solutions on each client assignment.<BR>Senior Associate Program Overview: Approximately the first six months of your employment will consist of a training period as a Junior Associate.&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon completion of the training period, Junior Associates will be expected to elevate to the Senior Associate position.<BR><BR>Key Responsibilities<BR>Junior Associate<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Complete fast-paced training program<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Develop ability to execute custom projects – consultations, surveys, and special projects<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Learn how to establish and grow relationships with thought leaders suited to assist GLG clients with their research requests<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Develop working knowledge of relevant industry dynamics<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Learn GLG's policies and procedures for protecting the integrity of client engagements<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Work collaboratively in partnerships to develop knowledge of client relationships<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Learn to:<BR>o&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Understand client research workflows and objectives<BR>o&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversee and manage client service process to ensure optimal satisfaction<BR>o&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Recommend premium experts, products, and services based on each client's specific research objectives<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Develop business acumen, time-management skills, professionalism, and communication skills <BR><BR>Senior Associate <BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Own full accountability and responsibility for select GLG clients by serving as a thought partner to design and deliver on custom projects – consultations, surveys, and special projects<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Work collaboratively in partnerships to ensure the growth and success of our highest priority clients.<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Establish and grow relationships with thought leaders suited to assist GLG clients with their research requests.&nbsp;&nbsp;<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Maintain substantive knowledge of relevant industry dynamics<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Implement GLG's policies and procedures for protecting the integrity of client engagements<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Work in collaborative interoffice teams to grow and promote client relationships<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Support the efforts of GLG's Business Development team to grow revenue through growth of existing business and pursuit of new business<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mentor new Research professionals<BR>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Develop and implement personal strategies to:<BR>o&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Understand client research workflows and objectives<BR>o&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oversee and manage client service process to ensure optimal satisfaction<BR>o&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Recommend premium experts, products, and services based on each client's specific research objectives<BR><BR>Required Skills<BR>Gerson Lehrman Group attracts employees from the most distinctive professional and academic backgrounds.&nbsp;&nbsp;Across all of our positions, we insist upon excellence, integrity, creativity, and professionalism. <BR><BR>For this position, we seek applicants with bachelors or masters degrees from top-tier colleges or universities, or equivalent work experience.&nbsp;&nbsp;The following factors will strengthen an applicant's candidacy:&nbsp;&nbsp;<BR> <BR>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Superior communication and interaction skills, including demonstrated oral, written and presentation abilities; <BR>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Demonstrated commitment and attention to detail, ideally in a high-volume, fast-paced environment; <BR>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Strong problem-solving skills; <BR>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Passion for fast-paced learning, especially in a technology-enabled environment; <BR>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Passion for sales and conversation, especially a successful track record in phone sales or outreach; <BR>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to communicate and manage relationships across the full professional spectrum including senior colleagues and extremely senior outside professionals; <BR>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Undergraduate or graduate GPA of 3.3 or better; and <BR>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Interest in building a business and in all business-building related activities. <BR><BR>Proficiency in any of the following languages a plus:&nbsp;&nbsp;German, French, Italian, Spanish, Russian, Chinese, Korean and/or Japanese.<BR><BR>Company Overview<BR>Gerson Lehrman Group, Inc. (GLG), founded more than ten years ago, began developing a network of leading experts to provide business decision-makers with insights to drive better, more informed outcomes. Initially serving investment firms, our company has grown to support professional services firms and corporations across every industry.<BR><BR>Today we connect hundreds of thousands of outstanding professionals and academics to each other through two distinct yet complementary platforms: GLG Research and G+.<BR><BR>GLG Research partners with investment firms, corporations and professional services firms that need targeted, on-demand expertise to help improve decision-making. GLG Research provides professional services and sophisticated web-based compliance systems to help our clients connect to the most relevant experts while managing potential conflicts. <BR><BR>G+ is our social business community for the world's most active and influential professionals, academics and entrepreneurs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Launched in the late second quarter of 2011, G+ provides a platform to start new conversations, ask important questions and propose ideas online and at in-person meetings. <BR><BR>GLG is headquartered in New York with 19 offices globally and over 700 employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;The company is backed by Bessemer Venture Partners and Silver Lake Partners.<BR><BR>For more information about GLG, please visit: www.gersonlehrmangroup.com<BR><BR>For more information about GLG Research, please visit: www.glgroup.com<BR><BR>Other Highlights<BR>Salary/Benefits: Competitive base salary plus eligibility for, depending on the role, a year-end performance-based discretionary bonus with comprehensive benefits program and a generous vacation and holiday schedule.<BR><BR>Notes:&nbsp;&nbsp;Gerson Lehrman Group, Inc. does not allow employees to trade stocks or any other security that may present a conflict of interest or appearance of conflict of interest. Gerson Lehrman Group, Inc. also requires that all employees sign a confidentiality and non-compete agreement with our firm. We conduct background checks on all prospective new hires.&nbsp;&nbsp;<BR><BR>Gerson Lehman Group, Inc. is an equal opportunity employer.<BR><BR>Please apply online at https://careers-gersonlehrmangroup.icims.com/jobs/1300/job
